content:
Ah, there's an extra curly brace in the package.json. Here's the corrected version:

```json
{
  "name": "paliostypescript",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "test": "jest",
    "build": "tsc"
  },
  "keywords": [],
  "author": "",
  "license": "ISC",
  "dependencies": {
    "@types/uuid": "^10.0.0",
    "firebase-admin": "^13.1.0",
    "uuid": "^11.1.0"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@types/jest": "^29.5.14",
    "@types/node": "^22.13.5",
    "jest": "^29.7.0",
    "ts-jest": "^29.2.6",
    "typescript": "^5.7.3"
  }
}
```

The error was caused by an extra curly brace after the scripts section. Try with this version and then you can run `npm run build`.
